<subpara id="RM000002D1F000X_01" type-id="01" category="01">
<s-1 id="RM000002D1F000X_01_0006" proc-id="RM0250U___0000C7X00000">
<ptxt>INSPECT SHIFT SOLENOID VALVE SL3</ptxt>
<content1 releasenbr="1">
<s2>
<ptxt>Measure the resistance according to the value(s) in the table below.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="G020767E29" width="2.775699831in" height="3.779676365in"/>
</figure>
<spec>
<title>Standard resistance</title>
<table>
<tgroup cols="2" align="center">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="2.07in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="2.06in"/>
<thead>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Specified Condition</ptxt>
<ptxt>20°C (68°F)</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>1 - 2</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>5.0 to 5.6 Ω</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</spec>
<ptxt>If the value is not as specified, replace the shift solenoid valve.</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>Connect the positive (+) lead to terminal 2 of the solenoid connector, and the negative (-) lead to terminal 1 of the solenoid connector.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>OK</title>
<specitem>
<ptxt>The solenoid valve makes an operating sound.</ptxt>
</specitem>
</spec>
<ptxt>If the result is not as specified, replace the shift solenoid valve.</ptxt>
</s2>
</content1>
</s-1>
